parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank rollover valve can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on busy roads.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off after filling the gas tank
the engine sputters or stalls at stop lights or stop signs
the vehicle stalls while driving
the gas pump shuts off every few seconds while filling the tank
fuel spills out of the filler pipe
the vehicle cannot be filled with fuel due to back pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag clock spring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbags may not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the horn may go off unexpectedly
and the airbags may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
and the airbags may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs can leave vehicles with safety defects on the road, putting drivers and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notifications but are unable to have the repairs done due to unavailable parts or delayed repair timelines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including the horn, airbags, headlights, and wipers, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The horn honks randomly
airbags do not deploy
headlights and wipers malfunction
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETC can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The throttle control warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the vehicle may jerk or hesitate while accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sunroof leak can cause water to enter the vehicle's electrical components, leading to malfunctions and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof
causing electrical components to malfunction
and potentially leading to radio failure
short circuits
and engine problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to come on and potentially prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
and the turn signal and radio display may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
the starter wire catches fire
and the radio may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPMS can cause the vehicle to lose air pressure, leading to tire blowouts and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The tire pressure light comes on
and the tire valve stem corrodes
causing air leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) and Stability Control Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and stability control systems can cause the vehicle to lose traction and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The ABS and stability control warning lights come on
and the vehicle may slow down or lose traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Front and Rear Subframes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front and rear subframes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in bodily harm or fatalities.
symptoms: The subframes are corroded
the tires are bent inward
the vehicle is unable to drive safely
the airbag module light comes on
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle shifts from one side to the other while driving
the vehicle loses rear control features while braking or accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in bodily harm or fatalities.
symptoms: The ball joints are bad
the vehicle is unsafe to drive
the tires are severely worn
the control arms are catastrophically failing
the vehicle is pulling to one side
the vehicle is veering out of control.
